Creating an empty file:

truncate -s 1MB filename
ls -l file name
truncate -s -1MB filename
truncate -s +1MB filename

dd if=/dev/zero of=filename bs=1024 count=1024
 to create 1MB file
dd if=/dev/zero of=filename bs=1024 count=1
 to create 1KB file
dd if=/dev/zero of=filename bs=1 count=1
 to create 1B file
dd if=/dev/zero of=filename bs=14MB count=1
 to create 14MB file
dd if=/dev/urandom of=filename bs=14MB count=1
